It is two or three weeks since I took my pen to write to you; Your last
from Paulghaut grieved me to see that you were so unwell, Samuel tells us
more about your health than yourself; dear son may the Lord soon restore
you fully, bless you and make you a blessing. I trust the rest, joy and the
means you had have been really blessed by our dear Lord so that you have
returned to your work with new strength and joy.
